ARD,Accessory navicular bone
What are the symptoms of Accessory navicular bone ?,"What are the signs and symptoms of Accessory navicular bone? Accessory navicular bone may cause no symptoms, but in some cases causes pain, tenderness, or irritation on or around the top of the instep. It may also cause the foot to be abnormally positioned, and may limit the normal motion of the foot. Symptoms may worsen with increased activity or tight shoes.
